<br>
Personally, my guild doesnt like usage of a pet on any of the mobs in the cursed cycle and on blood. <br>
I agree using a pet on cursed is risky and not worth the benifit of a few more dps, although i often argue with them theres no reason not to use a pet on the first two mobs mobs in cursed cycle and blood. <br>
<br>
Their reasoning is those mobs are hard to position so pets just cause a problem more than they help. Even though i tell them an attentive mage can use their pet as a boon to help positioning, and even though ive successfully used my pet on those mobs before without a hitch, they just dont see things my way.<br>
<br>
